| **Password** | System-generated (must change on first login) |

### Local Infrastructure

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Local Database** | `{{ local_infra_database | upper }}` |
| **Policies Schema** | `{{ local_policies_schema | upper }}` |

The local infrastructure database (`{{ local_infra_database | upper }}`) stores account-specific objects that cannot exist in the read-only replicated database. The policies schema (`{{ local_policies_schema | upper }}`) will contain authentication policies and other security configurations.

### Post-Creation Checklist

After the account is created:
- [ ] Initial administrator logs in and changes password
- [ ] Enable MFA for the administrator
- [ ] Add 1-2 additional ACCOUNTADMIN users for redundancy
- [ ] Consume the infrastructure database replication
- [ ] Create local infrastructure database and policies schema
- [ ] Configure security policies (network, authentication)